  "prompt": "What are the most commonly used slangs?",
  "response": "Slang terms can vary widely by region, age group, and subculture, but here are some commonly used slangs as of recent years:\n\n1. **Lit** - Exciting or excellent.\n2. **Salty** - Bitter or upset.\n3. **Flex** - To show off.\n4. **Ghost** - To abruptly cut off all communication.\n5. **GOAT** - Greatest of All Time.\n6. **Bae** - Term of affection, short for \"baby\" or \"before anyone else.\"\n7. **Thirsty** - Desperate for attention.\n8. **Squad** - Group of friends.\n9. **Basic** - Predictable, mainstream, or unoriginal.\n10. **Shade** - Disrespect or criticism.\n11. **Fam** - Close friends or family.\n12. **Vibe** - The atmosphere or feeling of a situation.\n13. **Stan** - An overly enthusiastic fan.\n\nSlangs evolve quickly, so some of these may fall out of fashion while new ones emerge.",
